# QuAIto

Digital Quarto board game built with React 19, TypeScript, and Vite.

## Stack overrides
- Single-view game; React Router is not used.
- Styling uses plain CSS files (`*.css`) with custom properties, not Tailwind.
- Import shared utilities from `@smart-games/common-spa` instead of duplicating them.

## File map
- `src/App.tsx` — game state, turn flow, AI orchestration, modals
- `src/utils/gameUtils.ts` — board helpers, win detection, piece generation
- `src/components/` — `GameBoard`, `Piece`, `PieceSet`, `ControlPanel`
- `src/ai.ts` — heuristic AI (`makeAIMove`, placement and piece-selection logic)
- `src/mcts/` — `@smart-games/mcts` worker entry, coordinator, state serialization

## Game modes
- Human vs Human, Human vs AI, AI vs AI (configured in `App.tsx` / control panel)

## Scope
- Only modify files under this app (`QuAIto/`).
- See also: `quaito-game-rules.mdc`, `quaito-ai.mdc`, `quaito-ui.mdc`.
